The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, May 8: TDSAT member J.S. Sarma is learnt to have been appointed the new chairman of the Telecom Regulatory Authority of India (Trai). The order on Sarmas taking over as the new Trai chief was issued after the appointment committee of the cabinet cleared his name. Sarma will succeed Nripendra Mishra, who retired on March 22.                             
	 New Delhi, May 8: Inflation increased for the third week in a row to 0.70 per cent on the back of a persistent rise in food items such as milk, cereals, pulses, vegetables and sugar. Wholesale price inflation rose 0.13 percentage points during the week ended April 25 from 0.57 per cent in the previous week.                             
	 New Delhi, May 8: The Supreme Court has imposed a total ban on mining activities in the eco-sensitive Aravalli ranges in Haryana, saying the degradation caused to the environment has become irreversible and extraordinary situation demands extraordinary remedies.                            
	 Mumbai, May 8: Bombay High Court has deferred till June 12 its order on the dispute between Jet Airways and Sahara India Commercial Corporation Ltd over a multi-crore takeover deal of erstwhile Sahara Airlines. This gives an opportunity to both sides to amicably settle the dispute.                                                                                                                           
